05:41.408 --> 05:47.480 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We take a closer look at Russia,
the president-elect,
and these latest revelations
with former attorney

05:47.514 --> 05:49.883 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
at the National Security Agency
Susan Hennessey.

05:49.916 --> 05:55.922 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She is now a fellow at the
Brookings Institution
and is managing editor for the
Web site Lawfare

05:55.956 --> 05:59.392 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
about the intersection of the
law and national
security.

05:59.426 --> 06:05.131 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And John Sipher, he served
almost 30 years
at the CIA, both in the agency's
clandestine

06:05.165 --> 06:07.334 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
service and executive ranks.

06:07.367 --> 06:13.206 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He was stationed in Moscow in
the 1990s and
he ran the CIA's Russia program
for three

06:13.240 --> 06:14.207 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
