06:14.241 --> 06:17.310 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He's now at CrossLead, a
consulting firm.

06:17.344 --> 06:19.045 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And welcome to both of you.

06:19.079 --> 06:22.115 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So let's start, Susan Hennessey,
but I just
want to ask both of you in
brief, what do

06:22.148 --> 06:23.149 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
you make of this report?

06:23.183 --> 06:24.851 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SUSAN HENNESSEY, Brookings
Institution: Right.

06:24.884 --> 06:28.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, for the moment, the real
story is the
allegations themselves are
unverified.

06:28.922 --> 06:31.725 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They're obviously quite
salacious in nature.

06:31.758 --> 06:35.829 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The real story is that the
intelligence community
thought it was appropriate to
brief the president

06:35.862 --> 06:37.430 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of the United States and the
president-elect.

06:37.464 --> 06:40.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That means that serious people
are taking
this seriously.

06:40.934 --> 06:45.672 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's different than saying
that the intelligence
community believes the
allegations or has

06:45.705 --> 06:47.440 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
substantiated them.

06:47.474 --> 06:51.478 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But this is a matter that is not
just simply
a matter of fake news or
something that we

06:51.511 --> 06:52.712 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
should disregard.

06:52.746 --> 06:55.982 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It clearly passes some degree of
preliminary
credibility.

06:56.016 --> 06:57.450 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: John Sipher, your
take?

06:57.484 --> 07:00.453 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN SIPHER, Former CIA Officer:
I think the
question is, is this real?

07:00.487 --> 07:03.823 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And there are things on the
positive side
and the negative side on that.

07:03.857 --> 07:08.028 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the positive side, for those
of us who
have lived and worked and worked
in Russia

07:08.061 --> 07:09.996 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and against the Russians, it
does feel right.

07:10.030 --> 07:12.432 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It does feel like the kind of
thing that Russians
do.

07:12.465 --> 07:14.067 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
A lot of those details fit.

07:14.100 --> 07:18.371 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Also, I think, the author has
some credibility,
which is on the positive side.

07:18.405 --> 07:20.940 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: This is the
former British
intelligence officer.

07:20.974 --> 07:21.941 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JOHN SIPHER: That's right.

07:21.975 --> 07:23.743 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Yes.

07:23.777 --> 07:26.413 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the negative side, it really
is hard to
make a distinction if we don't
know who those

07:26.446 --> 07:27.681 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
sources are.

07:27.714 --> 07:30.583 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He talks about his sources
providing various
information.

07:30.617 --> 07:34.421 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the CIA, before we would put
out a report
like that, an intelligence
report, there could

07:34.454 --> 07:38.825 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
be, you know, hundreds of pages
of information
on that person's access, on
their suitability,

07:38.858 --> 07:39.859 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on their personality.

07:39.893 --> 07:41.695 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We don't have that.

07:41.728 --> 07:45.865 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, secondly, the fact that a
lot of this
reporting is the presidential
administration

07:45.899 --> 07:49.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in Russia and the Kremlin is a
little bit
worrying, because, I mean,
that's essentially

07:50.003 --> 07:51.805 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a hard nut to crack.

07:51.838 --> 07:54.541 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And U.S. intelligence agencies
have been trying
to do that for years, and the
fact that he

07:54.574 --> 07:58.144 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
has this much data about them
does put it
into question a little bit.

07:58.178 --> 08:01.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Susan Hennessey,
let's talk
about your organization,
Lawfare.

08:01.881 --> 08:04.984 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You had a copy of this, what,
several weeks
ago.

08:05.018 --> 08:10.223 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And you started looking into it,
decided not
to put it out, but you did look
into it.

08:10.256 --> 08:15.528 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
How did you go about figuring
out or trying
to figure out what's real and
what isn't here?

08:15.562 --> 08:17.364 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SUSAN HENNESSEY: Right.

08:17.397 --> 08:22.102 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, the document was shared with
us to -- so
that we could provide some
professional input

08:22.135 --> 08:24.404 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as to whether or not it was
credible.

08:24.437 --> 08:30.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As we were satisfied that the
relevant government
entities were aware of the
documents, and

08:31.010 --> 08:36.483 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
